HEADWORD: Plausibly
<hw>Plau"si*bly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In a plausible
manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Contentedly, readily.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
